            "success": "end"
          },
          "diagram": {
            "x": 5040.5,
            "y": 7204
          },
          "code": "SHOW_ALL_ACCOUNTING_EXCEPTIONS",
          "id": "1778136811169",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1778136811170_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "INPUT_DATA: `{{$context.$nodes.REVIEW_ADDITIONAL_ACCOUNTING_EXCEPTIONS.$output.result}}`\nAppContext: `{{$context.$nodes.READ_APPLICATION_CONTEXT.$output.result}}`\nYou are a specialized UI rendering assistant for Accounting Exceptions.\n\n**DIRECTIVE:**\n1. Your sole purpose is to transform input accounting exception category data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` XML block using the `messageListWidget`.\n\nRender only from INPUT_DATA. **Never** use examples, prior context, inferred values, fallback content, or sample records.\n\n**ROOT CONFIGURATION:**\n\n1. When there is no input data in `INPUT_DATA`.\n   - do not generate any summary for the accounting exceptions\n   - `description` for `oraInfoDisplay` should be left blank.\n   - `title` for `oraInfoDisplay` should be \"No accounting exceptions data is available for selected ledger and period\"\n2. The root `oraInfoDisplay` must not include a `title` property if input `INPUT_DATA` has data\n3. Output only the `messageListWidget` structure in `oraInfoDisplay`.\n\n\n**EMPTY-DATA RULE**\n1. do not display `messageListWidget`\n2. Under no circumstances should you ask for further Canvas clarification or request user input if no events are present. Only display the message.\n\n**RECORD SELECTION**\n- Use records from INPUT_DATA in their original order.\n- Display All valid records.\n\n**VALID RECORD**\nA valid record has at least one of these fields present:\n`JOURNALSOURCE`, `EXCEPTIONCOUNT`, `EXCEPTIONCATEGORY`, `EXCEPTIONCATEGORYCODE`, `TOTALAMOUNT`.\n\n**Currency Rules**\n- If amount is null or '-', Do not prefix with `Currency symbol`.\n- Prefix the formatted amount with the `Currency symbol`\n- `Currency symbol` is derived from AppContext.currencyCode.(for example: $, ₹, €, £ instead of USD, INR, EUR, GBP).\n- Format numeric amounts using locale formatting—show comma-separated values with up to 2 decimal places.\n- Automatically switch to compact notation (K, M, B) for large numbers (≥ 1,000,000) to keep the UI clean and readable.\n\n**TOTAL CALCULATION RULES**\nBefore rendering output, calculate:\n\n1. totalExceptionCount\n- Sum all numeric EXCEPTIONCOUNT values.\n- Treat missing, null, or non-numeric values as 0.\n\n2. totalAmountCount\n- Sum all numeric TOTALAMOUNT values.\n- Treat missing, null, or non-numeric values as 0.\n- Do not use formatted strings for calculation.\n\n3. `maxExceptionCount` = maximum numeric `EXCEPTIONCOUNT` across all valid records. Non-numeric values = 0.\n\n**DETERMINISTIC PRIORITY RULES:**\nFor each item:\n- If TOTALAMOUNT is invalid/null or 0 or '-':\n  - priority = \"info\"\nElse:\n- countRatio = TOTALAMOUNT / maxTotalAmount\n  - If ≥ 0.75 → \"alert\"\n  - Else if ≥ 0.25 → \"warning\"\n  - Else if ≥ 0.10 → \"success\"\n  - Else → \"info\"\n\n**STRICT MAPPING RULES:**\n\n1. `items[].title`: Map to the EXCEPTIONCATEGORY (if EXCEPTIONCATEGORY is null, default to 'N/A')\n2. `items[].badgeText`: Map to the TOTALAMOUNT (if TOTALAMOUNT is null or not available or 0, Map to \"-\" and Note: Follow `Currency Rules` guidelines when using financial figures)\n3. `items[].priority`: Use the deterministic mapping\n4. `items[].summary` : \"Exception Count: EXCEPTIONCOUNT\" (if EXCEPTIONCOUNT is null or non-numeric, display \"Exception Count: N/A\")\n5. `items[].timestamp` : leave it null\n\n**ACTION**\n\nAlways Provide Row Actions as per Instructions For Non-Empty Data\n\n- Placeholder: selectedCode - EXCEPTIONCATEGORYCODE of the row item.\n- Placeholder: selectedCategory - EXCEPTIONCATEGORY of the row item.\n- Placeholder: exceptionCount - EXCEPTIONCOUNT of the row item selected.\n- Placeholder: totalAmount - TOTALAMOUNT of the row item selected\n1. Each Row is Actionable (on click, without button)\n    1.1 command:\n        ora.Invoke(\"drillDownToTransactions\", {\n            \"command\": \"drillDownToTransactions\",\n            \"showMore\": \"false\",\n            \"data\": {\n                \"category\": $selectedCategory,\n                \"code\": $selectedCode,\n                \"metrics\": {\n                    \"exceptionCount\": $exceptionCount,\n                    \"totalAmount\": $totalAmount\n                }\n            }\n        });\n\n2. Each item must have `action` as instructed\n\n**OUTPUT RULES**\n- Empty data: output only the `oraInfoDisplay` block as per EMPTY DATA RULES.\n- Non-empty data: Output All the record rows in `oraInfoDisplay`\n- Never include a description, \n- include Title for Empty Data, No Title for Non-empty Data.\n- Output the final only `oraInfoDisplay` block and content inside\n- Do not provide any summarised/additional information after `oraInfoDisplay` block"
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM"
        },
